'''''Ashkeron!''''' is an [[interactive fiction]] video game developed by [[Dorset]]-based Texgate Computers and published by [[Mirrorsoft]] for the [[Amstrad CPC]] and [[ZX Spectrum]] in 1985.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Attention All Spectrum Users - Basic Trace |journal=[[Popular Computing Weekly]] |date=19-25 May 1983 |volume=2 |issue=20 |page=42 |publisher=[[Sunshine Publications]]}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
The player character is Stephen the Blacksmith who is set to recover five treasures from the castle of an evil wizard. The game has a graphic feature called "walk-thru" where screen pictures scroll in the direction the player travels. The game supports joystick control and has a randomising option where the objects appear in different places in each playthrough.<ref name="YS"/>

